"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/924099","Department for Transport","false","2018-06-21","<p>In the Appraisal of Sustainability (AoS) that accompanies the proposed Airports National Policy Statement (NPS), the Government has undertaken a high level assessment of the effect on the water environment of the Heathrow Northwest Runway scheme.</p><p> </p><p>The proposed Airports NPS sets out the requirements in relation to water quality and resources which any applicant for a Development Consent Order would need to meet. This potentially includes the effects on water bodies or protected areas under the Water Framework Directive.</p><p> </p><p>The Government has not estimated the time it will take to decontaminate land. This a matter that would need to be addressed as part of any application for development consent. The AoS identifies a range of sources and pathways for contamination within the site boundary. These include two active landfills, 16 historic landfills and 11 registered pollution incidents, five of which are classified as significant.</p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman","153796 ; 153797","2018-06-21T16:24:39.363Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/924099/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/924099/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/924099/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-06-14","Heathrow Airport: Construction","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, whether his Department has estimated the quantity of contaminated land that will need to be decontaminated before a third runway can be constructed at Heathrow.","false","Biography information for Adam Afriyie","Windsor","Adam Afriyie","153798"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/924100","Department for Transport","false","2018-06-21","<p>The Government has not sought to identify specific like for like energy from waste facilities to manage the loss of the Lakeside plant. DEFRA’s assessment used publicly available data on waste disposal held by the Environment Agency to confirm that the Lakeside energy from waste plant is not a strategic asset.</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2018-06-21T16:27:10.93Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/924100/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/924100/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/924100/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-06-14","Lakeside Energy from Waste","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, whether his Department has identified waste disposal facilities in south-east England with like-for-like spare capacity to deal with the closure of Lakeside Energy from Waste in the event of a third runway being constructed at Heathrow.","false","Biography information for Adam Afriyie","Windsor","Adam Afriyie","153799"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/924101","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-06-22","<p>The national provider framework for the provision of ‘Healthier You: The NHS Diabetes Prevention Programme’ is expected to be re-tendered during 2018/19. Delivery of the NHS Diabetes Prevention Programme through remote and digital means is expected to form part of the service delivery requirements under the new Framework.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2018-06-22T10:24:43.877Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/924101/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/924101/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/924101/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-06-14","Diabetes: Preventive Medicine","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what plans are in place for that national roll-out of the digital interventions being piloted as part of the NHS Diabetes Prevention Programme digital stream.","false","Biography information for Royston Smith","Southampton, Itchen","Royston Smith","153903"
