"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923343","Cabinet Office","false","2018-06-27","<p>I am confident that the scope of the cabinet Secretary’s review was thorough.</p>","Norwich North","Chloe Smith",,"2018-06-27T10:44:00.367Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923343/answer","Biography information for Chloe Smith","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923343/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923343/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2018-06-13","Operation Blue Star","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what assessment he has made of the adequacy of the scope of the Heywood review into the Amritsar massacre in June 1984.","false","Biography information for Mr Tanmanjeet Singh Dhesi","Slough","Mr Tanmanjeet Singh Dhesi","153429"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923344","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-06-18","<p>The British Government acknowledges the strength of the feeling in the Sikh community regarding events of 1984. I am confident that the Cabinet Secretary's review of British advice to the Indian Army in advance of the events at Amritsar in 1984 was thorough and the British Government has no plans to establish a further inquiry.</p>","Cities of London and Westminster","Mark Field",,"2018-06-18T16:04:37.26Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923344/answer","Biography information for Mark Field","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923344/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923344/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-06-13","Operation Blue Star","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, when he plans to put in place an independent public inquiry into the Amritsar massacre in June 1984.","false","Biography information for Mr Tanmanjeet Singh Dhesi","Slough","Mr Tanmanjeet Singh Dhesi","153430"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923346","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-06-21","<p>Health Education England (HEE) published its first ever Cancer Workforce Plan in December 2017, which commits to the expansion of capacity and skills, including 200 clinical endoscopists and 300 reporting radiographers by 2021 and increasing the expansion of clinical nurse specialists so that every patient has access to a clinical nurse specialist or other support worker by 2021 by developing national competencies and a clear route into training. The 200 clinical endoscopists are in addition to the 200 by the end of 2018.</p><p> </p><p>Phase 2 of the Cancer Workforce Plan is being developed by HEE for consultation over summer 2018 and will take a longer-term view with a horizon of around 15 years.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2018-06-21T16:09:22.337Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923346/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923346/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923346/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-06-13","NHS: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what recent assessment he has made of the adequacy of the number of (a) specialist cancer nurses, (b) chemotherapy nurses, (c) palliative care nurses, (d) cancer support workers and (e) other diagnostic staff in the NHS.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","153224"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923347","Department for Transport","false","2018-06-21","<p>The average training length for a new train driver recruit will vary between Train Operating Companies, and will in part be determined by the complexity of the route(s) upon which the driver is being trained. However, we understand that training length can be up to or over a year. For existing drivers learning new routes, this will again vary depending upon factors such as the complexity of the route. The training of drivers for these new routes has been managed by the Train Operating Company who are best placed to answer queries around the specifics of the training detail. Route knowledge needs to be kept up to date and if a driver has not driven on a route for the past 6 months, they will need to undergo refresher training.</p><p> </p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2018-06-21T14:13:47.407Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923347/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923347/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923347/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-06-13","Southern","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how long the training is for drivers to learn new routes on Southern services arising from the new timetable; and what proportion of the route learning time for a new route is (a) classroom based and (b) learning on the job.","true","Biography information for Caroline Lucas","Brighton, Pavilion","Caroline Lucas","153242"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923348","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-06-20","<p>There is a responsibility on National Health Service trusts to make the very best use of all resources and items where they are safely and legally reusable and returnable.</p><p> </p><p>The policy on the return of equipment is a matter for each individual NHS trust. The policy should be included in the trust’s Sustainable Development Management Plan (SDMP). The publication of a trust’s SDMP is a requirement under Service Condition 18 of the NHS Standard Contract. This should be available for inspection by any member of the public.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2018-06-20T10:58:35.953Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923348/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923348/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923348/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-06-13","Medical Equipment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what steps his Department is taking to ensure that (a) heart monitors, (b) TENS machines and (c) mobility aids that are no longer required are returned for use by other patients.","false","Biography information for Mrs Anne Main","St Albans","Mrs Anne Main","153236"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923350","Department for Transport","false","2018-06-21","<p>The company standards regarding the safety, planning and measures for drivers to learn new routes are jointly managed by the Train Operating Company, Network Rail and the driver’s trade union ASLEF.</p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2018-06-21T14:16:37.07Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923350/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923350/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923350/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-06-13","Govia Thameslink Railway","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what discussions he has had with Govia Thameslink Railway on that company's standards for driver training of new routes; what assessment he has made of the adequacy of safety planning and measures in place for learning of new routes; and if he will make a statement.","true","Biography information for Caroline Lucas","Brighton, Pavilion","Caroline Lucas","153243"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923351","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-06-20","<p>The return, reuse or recycling of equipment is decided locally between the relevant commissioners and providers of equipment. There is a responsibility on National Health Service trusts to make the best use of all resources and items including recycling and reuse of equipment where it is safe and cost effective to do so.</p><p> </p><p>The Department does not collect data on expenditure on reusable medical equipment and no estimate has been made of these costs.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage","153238","2018-06-20T11:02:47.867Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923351/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923351/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923351/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-06-13","Medical Equipment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, whether his Department has plans to ensure that more medical equipment is returned and reused by other patients; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mrs Anne Main","St Albans","Mrs Anne Main","153237"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923352","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-06-20","<p>The return, reuse or recycling of equipment is decided locally between the relevant commissioners and providers of equipment. There is a responsibility on National Health Service trusts to make the best use of all resources and items including recycling and reuse of equipment where it is safe and cost effective to do so.</p><p> </p><p>The Department does not collect data on expenditure on reusable medical equipment and no estimate has been made of these costs.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage","153237","2018-06-20T11:02:47.913Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923352/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923352/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923352/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-06-13","Medical Equipment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what estimate his Department has made of the cost to the public purse of reusable medical equipment that was not returned in each of the last three years.","false","Biography information for Mrs Anne Main","St Albans","Mrs Anne Main","153238"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923353","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-06-18","<p>There are no plans to sell the Wave Class ships to Brazil. No further Wave Class ships will enter service as the Royal Fleet Auxiliary is receiving four Tide Class tankers: Tidespring, Tiderace, Tidesurge and Tideforce. These ships will support the Royal Navy over the next 10 years.</p>","Aberconwy","Guto Bebb","153441 ; 153443","2018-06-18T16:01:03.497Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923353/answer","Biography information for Guto Bebb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923353/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923353/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-06-13","Royal Fleet Auxiliary: Tankers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether he plans to sell any RFA Wave-class tankers to Brazil; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Luke Pollard","Plymouth, Sutton and Devonport","Luke Pollard","153440"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923355","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-06-18","<p>There are no plans to sell the Wave Class ships to Brazil. No further Wave Class ships will enter service as the Royal Fleet Auxiliary is receiving four Tide Class tankers: Tidespring, Tiderace, Tidesurge and Tideforce. These ships will support the Royal Navy over the next 10 years.</p>","Aberconwy","Guto Bebb","153440 ; 153443","2018-06-18T16:01:03.56Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923355/answer","Biography information for Guto Bebb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923355/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923355/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-06-13","Royal Fleet Auxiliary: Tankers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many Wave-class RFA tankers are planned to enter service with the Royal Fleet Auxiliary.","false","Biography information for Luke Pollard","Plymouth, Sutton and Devonport","Luke Pollard","153441"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923356","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-06-19","<p>European Union (EU) laws governing state aid do not apply to activity conducted outside the boundaries of the EU, however, the Ministry of Defence (MOD) makes no such distinction and treats all bidders who participate in its competitions equally.</p><p>State aid is generally prohibited under the Treaty of the Functioning of the EU, apart from under a few specific exemptions stipulated by legislation. Under EU and UK law, the mechanism available to the MOD for addressing state aid concerns is through the concept of an abnormally low tender, related to a specific competitive procurement. The MOD has the right to reject a tender if a grant of aid was not in accordance with EU and UK law.</p><p>The MOD takes open competition very seriously and is confident in the measures in place to ensure that the Fleet Solid Support ships' competitive process is conducted strictly in accordance with the EU regulations on state aid.</p>","Aberconwy","Guto Bebb",,"2018-06-19T15:01:33.267Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923356/answer","Biography information for Guto Bebb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923356/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923356/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-06-13","Royal Fleet Auxiliary","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether bids from (a) EU and (b) non-EU bidders for the RFA Solid Support Ship contract will have to demonstrate compliance with EU state aid rules.","false","Biography information for Luke Pollard","Plymouth, Sutton and Devonport","Luke Pollard","153442"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923357","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-06-18","<p>There are no plans to sell the Wave Class ships to Brazil. No further Wave Class ships will enter service as the Royal Fleet Auxiliary is receiving four Tide Class tankers: Tidespring, Tiderace, Tidesurge and Tideforce. These ships will support the Royal Navy over the next 10 years.</p>","Aberconwy","Guto Bebb","153440 ; 153441","2018-06-18T16:01:03.62Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923357/answer","Biography information for Guto Bebb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923357/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923357/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-06-13","Royal Fleet Auxiliary: Tankers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what estimate he has made of the number of RFA tankers the Royal Navy requires in order to service the (a) carrier strike and (b) other Royal Navy commitments over the next 10 years.","false","Biography information for Luke Pollard","Plymouth, Sutton and Devonport","Luke Pollard","153443"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923358","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-06-18","<p>The British Embassy in Ankara has engaged with the Turkish authorities about returning Anna Campbell's body to her family and with the International Red Cross. Due to the situation on the ground it is extremely difficult to confirm the whereabouts of any British nationals in Syria. We continue to stress to Turkey the importance of ensuring that the UN and non-governmental organisation partners are able to operate in areas under Turkish control. We stand ready to engage further with the authorities should the situation change.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2018-06-18T14:55:55.207Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923358/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923358/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923358/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-06-13","Anna Campbell","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what representations he has made to (a) the Turkish Government and (b) other organisations on returning Anna Campbell's body to her family.","false","Biography information for Hilary Benn","Leeds Central","Hilary Benn","153193"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923359","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-06-18","<p>There is no specific guidance on how one would assess the use of an automatic insulin pump. Guidance for PIP assessment providers and case managers is regularly reviewed and updated where necessary. We will consider Activity 3 during the next review and update the guidance where appropriate.</p><p> </p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton",,"2018-06-18T16:27:46.667Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923359/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923359/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923359/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-06-13","Personal Independence Payment: Diabetes","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, if she will revise the guidance to personal independence payments decision makers in relation to descriptor 3 managing therapy or monitoring a health condition to clarify whether an automatic insulin pump is an aid or appliance for managing medication or monitoring a health condition.","false","Biography information for Grahame Morris","Easington","Grahame Morris","153245"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923360","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-06-18","<p>A glucose meter is not considered an aid under Activity 3 as it does not meet the statutory definition of an aid. An aid is a device which “improves, provides or replaces C’s (claimant’s) impaired function” (Social Security (Personal Independence Payment) Regulations 2013, regulation 2). Although a glucose meter is not considered an aid, if a claimant requires supervision, prompting or assistance to use such a device to manage medication or to monitor their health condition they could score under Activity 3.</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton",,"2018-06-18T14:39:57.98Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923360/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923360/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923360/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-06-13","Personal Independence Payment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, for what reasons a glucose machine is not considered to be an aid or an appliance for monitoring a health condition for the purpose of the awarding of points in relation to descriptor 3 for a claim for personal independence payments.","false","Biography information for Grahame Morris","Easington","Grahame Morris","153246"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923362","Home Office","false","2018-06-18","<p>The Government is considering a range of options for the future immigration system and will set out initial plans in due course. We will build a comprehensive picture of the needs and interests of all parts of the UK and look to develop a system which works for all.</p><p>We will ensure that decisions on the long-term arrangements are based on evidence. The commission that we asked the MAC to undertake is very much part of this. The MAC are due to report back by September 2018.</p><p>The Government has separately commissioned the MAC to undertake a review of the composition of the Shortage Occupation List.</p><p>st</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2018-06-18T17:01:52.67Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923362/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923362/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923362/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-06-13","Migrant Workers: Doctors","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what assessment he has made of the UK's requirement for international doctors specialising in mental health after the UK leaves the EU; and whether that requirement will form part of his Department’s review of the Tier 2 visa cap.","false","Biography information for Catherine McKinnell","Newcastle upon Tyne North","Catherine McKinnell","153271"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923363","Home Office","false","2018-06-18","<p>On Friday 15 June, the Government announced changes to the allocation of places within the Tier 2 (General) cap of 20,700. The change – which will be implemented through amended Immigration Rules coming into effect on 6 July – will ensure that all doctors and all nurses needed in the UK will be able to be recruited to work here without being counted against the cap. This is intended to be a temporary change which recognises the importance of alleviating pressure on the NHS and which creates extra space within the cap for other sectors of the economy.</p><p>As part of this announcement, we will be asking the independent Migration Advisory Committee (MAC) to review the full composition of the Shortage Occupation List.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes","153273","2018-06-18T17:03:52.187Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923363/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923363/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923363/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-06-13","Migrant Workers: Health Professions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, if he will make an assessment of the potential effect of the review of the Tier 2 visa cap on healthcare in the North East.","false","Biography information for Catherine McKinnell","Newcastle upon Tyne North","Catherine McKinnell","153272"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923364","Home Office","false","2018-06-18","<p>On Friday 15 June, the Government announced changes to the allocation of places within the Tier 2 (General) cap of 20,700. The change – which will be implemented through amended Immigration Rules coming into effect on 6 July – will ensure that all doctors and all nurses needed in the UK will be able to be recruited to work here without being counted against the cap. This is intended to be a temporary change which recognises the importance of alleviating pressure on the NHS and which creates extra space within the cap for other sectors of the economy.</p><p>As part of this announcement, we will be asking the independent Migration Advisory Committee (MAC) to review the full composition of the Shortage Occupation List.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes","153272","2018-06-18T17:03:52.233Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923364/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923364/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923364/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-06-13","Psychiatry: Migrant Workers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, if he will make an assessment of the potential merits of adding child and adolescent psychiatrists, including higher trainees, to the Shortage Occupation List.","false","Biography information for Catherine McKinnell","Newcastle upon Tyne North","Catherine McKinnell","153273"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923365","Department for Transport","false","2018-06-21","<p>The Office of Rail and Road (ORR) is independent of government and accountable directly to Parliament. Within this framework, Ministers and senior officials of the Department for Transport meet with ORR’s Chair and Chief Executive regularly to discuss the measures ORR is taking to monitor and regulate the performance of Network Rail, including the Network Rail Monitor, which provides a comprehensive assessment of the company’s performance.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2018-06-21T13:50:07.97Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923365/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923365/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923365/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-06-13","Network Rail","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what recent assessment he has made of the effectiveness of the Office for Rail and Road in (a) monitoring and (b) regulating the performance of Network Rail in (i) 2017 and (ii) 2018.","false","Biography information for Andy McDonald","Middlesbrough","Andy McDonald","153286"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923366","Department for Transport","false","2018-06-21","<p>At the request of the Secretary of State for Transport, a full independent inquiry is being undertaken by the Office of Rail and Road, chaired by Professor Stephen Glaister and a final report is due by the end of 2018. The Department will take account of any recommendations the review makes to improve the functions and effectiveness all the key rail bodies, including the Department for Transport. In parallel with this inquiry, the Department will assess whether its franchisees have met their contractual obligations in respect of planning and delivering timetable change. Where franchisees are found to be materially in breach of their contractual obligations the Department will take the appropriate enforcement action against them.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2018-06-21T13:55:03.557Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923366/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923366/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923366/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-06-13","Railways: Standards","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what assessment he has made of the effectiveness of his Department in its monitoring of the performance of (a) Arriva Rail North and (b) Govia Thameslink Railway; and whether he has plans to improve mechanisms for that monitoring.","false","Biography information for Andy McDonald","Middlesbrough","Andy McDonald","153287"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923367","Department for Transport","false","2018-06-21","<p>Network Rail’s membership fee to Rail Delivery Group is determined on an annual basis. The fee for the last two years are:</p><p> </p><p>2016/17 £2.695m</p><p>2017/18 £2.760m</p><p> </p><p>Direct Rail Services do not pay membership fees.</p><p> </p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2018-06-21T13:44:39.54Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923367/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923367/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923367/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-06-13","Rail Delivery Group: Membership","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how much (a) Network Rail and (b) Direct Rail Services have spent on Rail Delivery Group membership fees since October 2016.","false","Biography information for Andy McDonald","Middlesbrough","Andy McDonald","153288"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923369","Department for Transport","false","2018-06-21","<p>The Department for Transport currently has no plans to ask The Office for Rail and Road to review this particular licence condition. The Office of Rail and Road published a consultation on updating the Network Licence under which it holds Network Rail to account, on 12 June. However, the consultation does not propose any changes to the Rail Delivery Group requirement.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2018-06-21T13:52:08.707Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923369/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923369/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923369/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-06-13","Rail Delivery Group: Membership","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what plans he has to instruct the Office for Rail and Road to review the licence conditions of (a) Network Rail, (b) passenger operators and (c) freight operators whereby it is mandatory to become a licensed member of the Rail Delivery Group and to comply with the obligations of membership as set out in the RDG articles of association.","false","Biography information for Andy McDonald","Middlesbrough","Andy McDonald","153289"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923370","Department for Transport","false","2018-06-21","<p>The licence condition that stipulates membership of Rail Delivery Group (RDG) ensures that freight and passenger operators and Network Rail are united in delivering a long-term vision for the network as a whole, and that farebox revenue across the network is properly settled and distributed. The condition requires that organisations become licensed members of the RDG, and not necessarily fee-paying full members. However, licensed members can obtain full, fee-paying membership should they meet a turnover requirement of £100m per annum and following agreement by existing members.</p><p> </p><p>The Government is supportive of the Rail Delivery Group’s role of providing industry leadership in the railway to achieve better outcomes for rail users and taxpayers. We will continue to work closely with RDG to ensure they are well placed to provide the strategic leadership needed to deliver key reforms in the railway.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2018-06-21T14:06:56.183Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923370/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923370/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923370/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-06-13","Rail Delivery Group: Membership","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what assessment he has made of the (a) benefits and (b) value for money of the licence conditions for (i) Network Rail, (ii) passenger operators and (iii) freight operators whereby it is mandatory to become a licensed member of the Rail Delivery Group.","false","Biography information for Andy McDonald","Middlesbrough","Andy McDonald","153290"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923371","Department for Transport","false","2018-06-21","<p>The Department of Transport has asked Network Rail, as part of the development work for the Transpennine Route Upgrade, to provide options for freight capacity and capability on this route.</p><p> </p><p>This development work is still ongoing and no final decision will made on the scope of the upgrade, including options for freight, until the outline business case is completed and the costs, benefits and affordability are properly understood.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2018-06-21T13:47:22.93Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923371/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923371/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923371/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-06-13","Railways: North of England","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what assessment he has made of the effect of upgrades to the Northern Trans-Pennine routes on the availability of paths for (a) intermodal and (b) bulk rail freight traffic.","false","Biography information for Andy McDonald","Middlesbrough","Andy McDonald","153291"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923373","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-06-20","<p>There are various mechanisms in place for members of the public to make complaints about their town or parish council.</p><p>These include: using the parish council’s complaints procedure;raising the matter at the annual parish meeting; questioning, or making an objection to, the auditor during the public inspection period of accounts; or by joining with a group of local electors to call for a parish poll on the issue. In instances of councillor misconduct, complaints can be made to the principal council’s monitoring officer who can investigate.</p><p>Central Government does not have the power to intervene in parish council matters and believes that the current local system of redress is proportionate to the sector and consistent with this Government's principles on localism.</p>","Richmond (Yorks)","Rishi Sunak",,"2018-06-20T13:16:51.29Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923373/answer","Biography information for Rishi Sunak","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923373/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923373/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-06-13","Parish Councils: Complaints","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, what mechanism is in place for members of the public to raise complaints about the operation of town and parish councils; and to which body such complaints should be directed.","false","Biography information for Daniel Kawczynski","Shrewsbury and Atcham","Daniel Kawczynski","153235"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923374","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-06-20","<p>The UK provides military support to its NATO Allies in many ways, and the next 12 months will be no different. For example, in Estonia the UK will continue to be the Framework Nation for NATO's enhanced Forward Presence, with an 800-strong armoured battlegroup deployed there. We will also conduct Air Policing from Estonia and Iceland in 2019. In addition, UK forces will take part in range of exercises and training activities with their Estonian and Icelandic counterparts.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2018-06-20T15:07:14.173Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923374/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923374/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923374/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-06-13","Military Aid","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what plans his Department has to provide military support to NATO allies in (a) Estonia and (b) Iceland in the next 12 months.","false","Biography information for Dr Matthew Offord","Hendon","Dr Matthew Offord","153251"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923375","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-06-19","<p>With last month's investment of £960 million into its second delivery phase, the Dreadnought programme remains on schedule to deliver the first of class in the early 2030s and is within the £31 billion cost estimated in the 2015 Strategic Defence and Security Review.</p>","Aberconwy","Guto Bebb",,"2018-06-19T14:57:38.807Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923375/answer","Biography information for Guto Bebb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923375/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923375/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-06-13","Trident Submarines","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what progress has been made on the Royal Navy's Dreadnought submarine programme.","false","Biography information for Dr Matthew Offord","Hendon","Dr Matthew Offord","153252"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923376","Department for Transport","false","2018-06-18","<p>The Appraisal of Sustainability (AoS) that accompanies the proposed Airports National Policy Statement (NPS) provides a strategic level assessment of the potential social, economic, and environmental impacts of expansion, including on air quality. The AoS has been published on the DfT’s website and the relevant information can be found at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/appraisal-of-sustainability-for-the-proposed-airports-national-policy-statement" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/appraisal-of-sustainability-for-the-proposed-airports-national-policy-statement</a></p><p> </p><p>Should the proposed Airports NPS be designated, then it would be for the promoter to undertake a detailed assessment of the air quality effects of the scheme, and put forward an appropriate package of mitigation measures.</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2018-06-18T15:44:20.983Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923376/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923376/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923376/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-06-13","Heathrow Airport: Air Pollution","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what assessment he has made of the effect of expansion at Heathrow Airport on (a) particulate emissions and (b) nitrogen oxide levels.","false","Biography information for Zac Goldsmith","Richmond Park","Zac Goldsmith","153262"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923377","Department for Transport","false","2018-06-18","<p>The Department for Transport has estimated the number of additional local jobs expected to be created by airport expansion in both 2030 and 2050. The Heathrow Northwest Runway scheme is expected to generate between 57,000 and 114,000 additional local jobs by 2030, and between 39,000 and 78,000 additional local jobs by 2050.</p><p> </p><p>Additional jobs are a result of higher passenger traffic being generated at the airport. Expansion at Heathrow will lead to a significant increase in passenger numbers, which will continue beyond 2050. This is expected to create local jobs that are sustainable in the long-run.</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2018-06-18T13:45:13.297Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923377/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923377/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923377/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-06-13","Heathrow Airport: Job Creation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what assessment he has made of the long-term sustainability of any jobs created by expansion at Heathrow Airport.","false","Biography information for Zac Goldsmith","Richmond Park","Zac Goldsmith","153263"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923378","Department for Transport","false","2018-06-18","<p>Airport charges at Heathrow Airport have fallen by almost £2 per passenger in real terms since 2014. In the context of expansion, the Civil Aviation Authority will determine an appropriate level of airport charges in line with its statutory duty to further the interest of consumers. The Secretary of State also set out a clear ambition in 2016 for airport charges to remain as close as possible to current levels.</p><p> </p><p>The Airports Commission found that if there were any increase in charges at Heathrow as a result of expansion this would likely be absorbed by airlines, with passenger fares remaining unaffected or even falling further after the capacity constraints are released. The Government is also clear that the expansion of Heathrow will provide a significant boost to passengers and the wider economy even if airport charges were to increase modestly, and were passed on to passengers.</p><p> </p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2018-06-18T15:20:00.897Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923378/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923378/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923378/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-06-13","Heathrow Airport","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what assessment he has made of the effect of higher landing charges at Heathrow Airport on (a) the UK's and (b) Heathrow Airport's global competitiveness.","false","Biography information for Zac Goldsmith","Richmond Park","Zac Goldsmith","153264"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923380","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-06-19","<p>The Armed Forces are proactively recruiting and training individuals as engineers and intelligence specialists to meet the needs of Defence. There is a competitive market for such skills and we have introduced a range of measures to support our recruitment and retention efforts. These include remunerative measures such as targeted Golden Hellos and enhanced bursary schemes; the use of specialist recruiting teams, enhanced digital marketing campaigns, pioneering lateral entry at more senior grades for trained professionals and accelerated apprenticeship schemes.</p><p>In addition, and distinct from recruiting, the Ministry of Defence is fully engaged in youth STEM outreach activity as part of the UK national effort, to ensure that the talent pipeline has sufficient numbers from which then to recruit. This is underpinned by the launch of the Defence Youth STEM engagement strategy in 2016, and subsequent support to cross-Government initiatives such as the Department for Transport led Year of Engineering and the Department for Education led STEM oversight board.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2018-06-19T15:03:59.883Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923380/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923380/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923380/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-06-13","Armed Forces: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what steps his Department is taking to recruit (a) more engineers and (b) intelligence specialists in the armed forces.","false","Biography information for Dr Matthew Offord","Hendon","Dr Matthew Offord","153253"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923381","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-06-21","<p>General practitioners are responsible for ensuring their own clinical knowledge remains up-to-date and for identifying learning needs as part of their continuing professional development. This activity should include taking account of new research and developments in guidance, such as that produced by the National Institute for Health and Care Excellence (NICE), to ensure that they can continue to provide high quality care to all patients. NICE published a guideline on the diagnosis and management of menopause in November 2015 that includes recommendations on the prescribing of hormone replacement therapy.</p><p> </p><p>All United Kingdom-registered doctors are expected to meet the professional standards set out in the General Medical Council’s (GMC) ‘Good Medical Practice’. In 2012 the GMC introduced revalidation which supports doctors in regularly reflecting on how they can develop or improve their practice, gives patients confidence doctors are up to date with their practice and promotes improved quality of care by driving improvements in clinical governance.</p><p> </p><p>The training curricula for postgraduate trainee doctors is set by the relevant medical Royal College and has to meet the standards set by the GMC. While curricula do not necessarily highlight specific conditions for doctors to be aware of, they instead emphasise the skills and approaches that a doctor must develop in order to ensure accurate and timely diagnoses and treatment plans for their patients.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2018-06-21T16:11:42.8Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923381/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923381/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923381/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-06-13","Menopause","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what steps his Department is taking to improve the training GPs receive on the treatment of menopausal symptoms and the prescription of hormone replacement therapy.","false","Biography information for Rachel Maclean","Redditch","Rachel Maclean","153438"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923382","Treasury","false","2018-06-21","<p>Officials meet regularly with stakeholders from across the bookmaking sector to hear their views on the gambling market, and a range of economic and policy issues.</p><p> </p><p>Details of ministerial meetings with external bodies are published at <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/hmt-ministers-meetings-hospitality-gifts-and-overseas-travel" target="_blank">HMT ministers' meetings, hospitality, gifts and overseas travel - GOV.UK</a></p><p> </p>","Newark","Robert Jenrick",,"2018-06-21T14:57:28.89Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923382/answer","Biography information for Robert Jenrick","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923382/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923382/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2018-06-13","Bookmakers","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, which bookmaker organisations his Department has met with in 2018.","false","Biography information for Carolyn Harris","Swansea East","Carolyn Harris","153396"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923383","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-06-21","<p>Public Health England (PHE) has not funded any bowel cancer screening awareness campaigns.</p><p> </p><p>PHE’s Be Clear on Cancer campaigns aim to raise the public’s awareness of signs and symptoms of cancer, and are an important step in helping to diagnose cancers earlier. In 2017, PHE collaborated with Cancer Research UK (CRUK) to deliver a jointly-branded, Be Clear on Cancer/CRUK pilot screening campaign in the North West of England to promote the uptake of bowel screening. The campaign was funded by CRUK.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2018-06-21T16:14:29.95Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923383/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923383/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923383/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-06-13","Bowel Cancer: Screening","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, how much of the Public Health England budget has been spent on bowel cancer screening awareness campaigns in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Rehman Chishti","Gillingham and Rainham","Rehman Chishti","153248"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923384","Department for Education","false","2018-06-21","<p>In 2016/17, 11.2 per cent of apprenticeship starts were from a black, Asian, and minority ethnic (BAME) background. This is the highest reported over the past seven years, and considerably higher than the previous year of 10.5 per cent, but there is still more to do.</p><p>In February we launched a new partnership with five major cities in England, supported by city mayors, to make sure apprenticeships are accessible to individuals from all backgrounds.</p><p>Our Apprenticeship Diversity Champions Network, now comprised of over 55 members, continues to influence the behaviour of other employers to support more people from underrepresented groups, including members of BAME communities, to access apprenticeships.</p><p>Statistics covering latest in-year data relating to apprenticeships can be found at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/further-education-and-skills-march-2018" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/further-education-and-skills-march-2018</a>.</p>","Guildford","Anne Milton",,"2018-06-21T12:52:05.667Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923384/answer","Biography information for Anne Milton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923384/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923384/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-06-13","Apprentices: Ethnic Groups","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what progress the Government has made in increasing BAME participation in apprenticeships in line with its BAME 2020 vision to increase participation by 20 per cent.","false","Biography information for Rehman Chishti","Gillingham and Rainham","Rehman Chishti","153249"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923385","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-06-18","<p>All general practitioners (GPs) receive mental health training as part of their postgraduate general practice training, based on curricula set by the Royal College of General Practitioners, to standards set by the General Medical Council.</p><p> </p><p>Health Education England (HEE) is currently looking at ways to provide further additional training as part of the Foundation Programme whilst also ensuring a balanced curriculum given the wide range of skills and experience GPs need to gain in their education and training.</p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price",,"2018-06-18T14:17:23.377Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923385/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923385/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923385/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-06-13","General Practitioners: Training","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what plans the Government has to expand mental health training as part of the GP training programme.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","153254"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923386","Department for Transport","false","2018-06-18","<p>This was an operational decision taken by Northern and accepted by Transport for the North as the best temporary solution for passengers.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2018-06-18T15:02:51.603Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923386/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923386/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923386/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-06-13","Lakes Railway Line","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, whether he approved the request of Arriva Northern for an extension of the Lakes Line suspension.","false","Biography information for Tim Farron","Westmorland and Lonsdale","Tim Farron","153239"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923387","Department for Transport","false","2018-06-18","<p>The Lakes Line suspension was an operational decision taken by Northern and accepted by Transport for the North as the best temporary solution for passengers.</p><p> </p><p>The Transport Secretary has been very clear however that this line must be open as soon as possible to allow people to use a reliable train service again.</p><p> </p><p>Northern are working with local stakeholders with a view to reintroducing a shuttle train service on the Lakes Line as early as possible.</p><p> </p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2018-06-18T15:00:07.5Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923387/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923387/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923387/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-06-13","Lakes Railway Line","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what plans he has to approve a further extension of the Lakes Line suspension.","false","Biography information for Tim Farron","Westmorland and Lonsdale","Tim Farron","153240"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923388","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-06-18","<p>The information requested is not collected centrally.</p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price",,"2018-06-18T14:15:04.993Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923388/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923388/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923388/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-06-13","Prisons: Mental Health Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, how many people have been employed by mental health in-reach teams in prisons in the most recent financial year for which information is available.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","153255"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923390","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-06-18","<p>Due to the integrated approach to prison healthcare services commissioning by NHS England, this information is not available in the format requested.</p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price",,"2018-06-18T14:13:55.227Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923390/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923390/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923390/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-06-13","Prisons: Drugs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, how much has been spent from the public purse on drug rehabilitation services in prisons in the most recent financial year for which information is available.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","153256"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923391","Department for International Development","false","2018-06-18","<p>The Secretary of State for International Development and Foreign Secretary wrote a joint letter on 20 March to Prime Minister Sheikh Hasina, asking her to save as many lives as possible by allocating additional land at lower risk of flooding and landslides, reducing density in the existing camps, and having evacuation plans in place. Minister Field made the same request to Minister of State Shahriar Alam on 27 March, and to Foreign Minister Ali on 19 April.</p><p> </p><p>Following a visit by the United Nations Security Council to Bangladesh and Burma from 28 April – 1 May, we supported a UNSC press statement encouraging the international community to increase support to the Government of Bangladesh for emergency preparedness measures. We continue to work with the Government of Bangladesh and international agencies to support.</p><p> </p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2018-06-18T14:29:13.827Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923391/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923391/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923391/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2018-06-13","Bangladesh: Rohingya","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, pursuant to the Answer of 26 April 2018 to Question 136643 on Bangladesh: Rohingya, if she will make representations to the Prime Minister of Bangladesh supporting the UNHCR request that more flat land be made available to relocate families who are in danger of the effects of monsoons in that country.","false","Biography information for Sarah Champion","Rotherham","Sarah Champion","153285"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923393","Department for Transport","false","2018-06-18","<p>The Rail North Partnership team that manages the franchise on behalf of Transport for the North and the Department is currently working with Northern to reintroduce a train service on the Lakes Line as early as possible. Northern have been consulting with Cumbria County Council on reinstating services.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2018-06-18T16:13:29.097Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923393/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923393/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923393/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-06-13","Lakes Railway Line","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, if he will instruct Arriva Northern to run a shuttle service on the Lakes line instead of suspending services on that line.","false","Biography information for Tim Farron","Westmorland and Lonsdale","Tim Farron","153241"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923394","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-06-18","<p>The information requested is not collected centrally.</p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price",,"2018-06-18T14:12:40.89Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923394/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923394/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923394/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-06-13","Prisoners: Suicide","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, how many self-inflicted deaths there were of former prisoners in England within 14 days of their release in 2017.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","153257"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923395","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-06-18","<p>The Prisons and Probation Ombudsman (PPO) spent approximately £1.3m on investigations into self-inflicted deaths in 2016-17 and £1.2m in 2017-18. This covers the salary costs of managers, investigators, and administrative staff including interview transcribers, family liaison officers, and fees for call-off investigators. It also includes travel and incidental expenses.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2018-06-18T15:01:43.733Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923395/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923395/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923395/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-06-13","Prisoners: Suicide","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how much the Prisons and Probation Ombudsman has spent on investigations into self-inflicted deaths in each of the last two years.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","153258"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923396","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-06-21","<p>Public Health England develops best practice guidance for the NHS Health Check programme. NHS Health Checks help identify people with familial hypercholesterolaemia (FH) and also raise awareness of the condition by ensuring those with a cholesterol level of 7.5mmol/L or higher, or a family history of a cardiac event under the age of 60, are referred for FH assessment. In the first five years of the NHS Health Check programme, 6,864,964 of the eligible population have received a check.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2018-06-21T16:08:01.217Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923396/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923396/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923396/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-06-13","Familial Hypercholesterolaemia","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what steps his Department is taking to raise awareness of familial hypercholesterolemia.","false","Biography information for Rehman Chishti","Gillingham and Rainham","Rehman Chishti","153250"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923397","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-06-20","<p>It is the responsibility of local providers and commissioners of NHS services to make the reasonable adjustments required by the Equality Act 2010 to ensure that disabled people, including those with sight and hearing impairments, are not placed at a substantial disadvantage compared to non-disabled people.</p><p> </p><p>Additionally, under the NHS Constitution, National Health Service organisations are required to provide high quality comprehensive services, based on clinical need, which do not discriminate between patients on the basis of disability, including sight and hearing impairments.</p><p> </p><p>In order to reduce the unacceptable variation in the provision of accessible information and communication support to disabled people, all organisations that provide NHS care or publicly-funded adult social care have been legally required to follow the Accessible Information Standard since 1 August 2016. This ensures that people with a disability, impairment or sensory loss are provided with information they can easily read or understand, with support, so they can communicate effectively with services. This will help ensure that they receive an improved standard of care and be more involved in how that care is delivered.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2018-06-20T11:04:18.083Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923397/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923397/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923397/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-06-13","Hearing Impairment and Visual Impairment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what steps his Department is taking to ensure that patients with sight and hearing impairments are able to access NHS services.","false","Biography information for Mrs Sharon Hodgson","Washington and Sunderland West","Mrs Sharon Hodgson","153225"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923398","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-06-18","<p>The information requested is not available.</p><p> </p><p>National Statistics on income-related benefit take-up (including Pension Credit) is published and available at:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/645577/income-related-benefits-estimates-of-take-up-2015-16.pdf" target="_blank">https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/645577/income-related-benefits-estimates-of-take-up-2015-16.pdf</a></p>","Hexham","Guy Opperman",,"2018-06-18T11:09:38.39Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923398/answer","Biography information for Guy Opperman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923398/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923398/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-06-13","Social Security Benefits: Religious Orders","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what assessment she has made of the take-up of (a) pension credit, (b) attendance allowance and (c)  other social security benefits by people who have served in or are maintained by a religious order.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","153202"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923399","Home Office","false","2018-06-21","<p>The first priority for any Windrush migrants that may have experienced problems in obtaining documents confirming their immigration status is to help them secure that status. That is why the Government quickly established the Windrush Taskforce, which has a dedicated team for vulnerable people.</p><p>The Taskforce has established a fast-track service for the payment of benefits, working closely in a co-ordinated manner with DWP.</p><p>The Government continues to urge any affected people to come forward to the Taskforce so that we can help them. Where people are identified as being homeless, wherever possible the Home Office has worked with Local Authorities to secure temporary accommodation.</p><p>A compensation scheme for those of the Windrush generation that might have been affected is in the process of being established. The call for evidence for that scheme ended on 8 June and the Home Office are now preparing to launch the next stage of consultation, working with affected communities. The scheme will be set up as soon as possible after we have consulted.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2018-06-21T15:53:53.507Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923399/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923399/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923399/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-06-13","Immigration: Windrush Generation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what assessment he has made of the potential merits of establishing a hardship fund to help the Windrush generation migrants with legal costs and other bills as a result of his Department's immigration policy.","false","Biography information for Kate Hollern","Blackburn","Kate Hollern","153302"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923400","Home Office","false","2018-06-21","<p>On Friday 15 June, the Government announced changes to the allocation of places within the Tier 2 (General) cap of 20,700. The change – which will be implemented through amended Immigration Rules coming into effect on 6 July – will ensure that all doctors and all nurses needed in the UK will be able to be recruited to work here without being counted against the cap. This is intended to be a temporary change which recognises the importance of alleviating pressure on the NHS and which creates extra space within the cap for other sectors of the economy.</p><p>As part of this announcement, we will be asking the independent Migration Advisory Committee (MAC) to review the full composition of the Shortage Occupation List.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2018-06-21T14:44:21.81Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923400/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923400/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923400/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-06-13","Visas: Skilled Workers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, when the Government plans to make changes to the Tier 2 visa system; and what assessment he has made of the potential merits of introducing specific visa system for the NHS.","false","Biography information for Kate Hollern","Blackburn","Kate Hollern","153303"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923401","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-06-18","<p>​The UK, as a Troop Contributing Country (TCC) to UN peacekeeping missions, receives reimbursements from the UN for equipment it has provided. These reimbursements fall into two categories: self-sustainment and major equipment. Self-sustainment can include items such as bedding and furniture. Major equipment can includes items such as generators, containers and vehicles. A full list of the equipment the UK has received reimbursement for, each year since 2013-14, is not held centrally by the FCO and could only be provided at a disproportionate cost.</p>","Cities of London and Westminster","Mark Field",,"2018-06-18T16:45:48.13Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923401/answer","Biography information for Mark Field","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923401/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923401/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-06-13","United Nations: Peacekeeping Operations","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, pursuant to the Answer of 4 June 2018 to Question 147856 on United Nations: peace keeping operations, if he will list the equipment that the UK received reimbursements for from the UN in each year since 2013-14.","false","Biography information for Nia Griffith","Llanelli","Nia Griffith","153227"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923403","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2018-06-21","<p>We are looking at the role of society lotteries, with advice from the Gambling Commission, and will make an announcement in due course.</p>","Chatham and Aylesford","Tracey Crouch",,"2018-06-21T10:03:02.407Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923403/answer","Biography information for Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923403/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923403/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2018-06-13","Lotteries: Regulation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, when he plans to announce proposals for the deregulation of Society Lotteries.","false","Biography information for Sir Henry Bellingham","North West Norfolk","Sir Henry Bellingham","153220"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923404","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-06-21","<p>No date has been set, but the Foreign Secretary still hopes to visit Zimbabwe in 2018.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2018-06-21T13:18:26.733Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923404/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923404/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923404/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-06-13","Zimbabwe: Visits Abroad","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, pursuant to the Answer of 26 April 2018 to Question 136506 on Zimbabwe: visits abroad, whether a date has now been set for his visit to Zimbabwe.","false","Biography information for Sir David Evennett","Bexleyheath and Crayford","Sir David Evennett","153203"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923405","Treasury","false","2018-06-18","<p>The information requested is not readily available and could be provided only at disproportionate cost.</p>","Newark","Robert Jenrick","153368 ; 153374","2018-06-18T15:31:09.727Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923405/answer","Biography information for Robert Jenrick","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923405/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923405/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2018-06-13","Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how much his Department spent on preparations for inter-governmental discussions in relation to negotiations with the EU in 2018 to date.","false","Biography information for Neil Gray","Airdrie and Shotts","Neil Gray","153304"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923406","Department for Education","false","2018-06-21","<p>There have been 40,650 apprenticeship starts for the Health, Public Services and Care sector subject area reported to date in the first half of the 2017/18 academic year (August 2017 to January 2018) in England: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistical-data-sets/fe-data-library-apprenticeships" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistical-data-sets/fe-data-library-apprenticeships</a>.</p><p>We want to increase the number of nursing apprenticeships and now have a complete apprentice pathway from entry level to postgraduate advanced clinical practice in nursing. This is a huge achievement in supporting people from all backgrounds to enter a nursing career in the NHS.</p><p>The registered nurse (degree) apprenticeship standard was approved for delivery on 9 May 2017. There were 20 total starts on the registered nurse (degree) apprenticeship reported to date in the 2017/18 academic year (August 2017 to January 2018) in England, of which fewer than five were started in London and Bexley.</p><p>We have also created a new programme for nursing associate apprentices to broaden the routes into the profession. 5,000 starts are planned in 2018, with a further 7,500 in 2019.</p><p>We are working very closely with ministers in the Department of Health and Social Care, along with employers and Health Education England to make sure that the NHS is able to recruit and benefit from apprentices in nursing and a number of other occupations.</p>","Guildford","Anne Milton",,"2018-06-21T14:04:27.65Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923406/answer","Biography information for Anne Milton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923406/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923406/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-06-13","Nurses: Apprentices","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many people have undertaken a nursing apprenticeship in (a) the London Borough of Bexley and (b) London in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Sir David Evennett","Bexleyheath and Crayford","Sir David Evennett","153204"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923407","Treasury","false","2018-06-18","<p>The government speaks regularly to a range of stakeholders on customs and related matters. Since the referendum, ministers and officials have met with over 300 businesses and other organisations involved in international trade throughout the UK to discuss customs VAT and excise.</p><p> </p><p>Businesses and representative bodies have an important role to play in the policy making process and the government will continue its engagement.</p><p> </p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride","153369 ; 153375","2018-06-18T14:18:39.793Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923407/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923407/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923407/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2018-06-13","Customs","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many representations he has received from (a) business organisations and (b) trade unions on customs arrangements after the UK leaves the EU; and how many of those such representations have received a response from his Department.","false","Biography information for Neil Gray","Airdrie and Shotts","Neil Gray","153305"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923408","Treasury","false","2018-06-18","<p>As part of our appraisal of energy projects, the Treasury and the Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy (BEIS) assess impacts on the local and UK economy. This is reflected in the Government assurance process for Hinkley Point C, and we continue to monitor the delivery of the project’s economic benefits with the developer. The developer expects the project will contribute £1.5 billion to the local economy during construction and 25,000 job opportunities, whilst up to 64% of the value of construction contracts will be received by UK companies.</p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss","153370 ; 153376","2018-06-18T13:12:16.627Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923408/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923408/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923408/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2018-06-13","Hinkley Point C Power Station","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what discussions he has had with the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy on the fiscal multiplier associated with the Hinkley C nuclear power station project relative to carbon capture and storage projects.","false","Biography information for Neil Gray","Airdrie and Shotts","Neil Gray","153306"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923409","Treasury","false","2018-06-18","<p>As has been the convention of successive governments, details of conversations between Secretaries of State are not normally disclosed.</p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss","153377","2018-06-18T13:14:42.467Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923409/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923409/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923409/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2018-06-13","Trident: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what discussions he has had with the Secretary of State for Defence on the relative fiscal multiplier of the trident weapons programme relative to other (a) army, (b) navy and (c) air force expenditure in Scotland.","false","Biography information for Neil Gray","Airdrie and Shotts","Neil Gray","153307"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923410","Treasury","false","2018-06-18","<p>Treasury Ministers and officials receive representations from a wide variety of organisations in the public and private sectors as part of the process of policy development and delivery.</p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss","153378","2018-06-18T13:06:19.86Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923410/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923410/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923410/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2018-06-13","Public Expenditure: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many representations he has received from (a) business organisations and (b) trade unions on changes to the Scottish Government block grant since 2010; and how many of those representations have received a response from his Department.","false","Biography information for Neil Gray","Airdrie and Shotts","Neil Gray","153308"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923411","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-06-18","<p>Postcode district information, based on primary contact addresses, for recruits who have attended AFC Harrogate over the last three financial years (FY) is set out in the attached table.</p><p>Individuals from 48 Northern Ireland postcode districts have attended Harrogate over the last three years, in compliance with security requirements these have been grouped into one postcode area.</p><p> </p><p>To limit disclosure and ensure confidentiality numbers fewer than five are represented by '~'. Figures have been rounded to the nearest 5 and zero is represented by '-'.</p><p> </p><p>These figures are Single Service estimates and are not official statistics produced by Defence Statistics.</p><p> </p><p>Only UK postcodes have been included.</p>","Aberconwy","Guto Bebb",,"2018-06-18T16:51:58.467Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923411/answer","Biography information for Guto Bebb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923411/answer","153416 - Liz Saville Roberts.docx","153416 - Postcodes for AFC Harrogate Recruits","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923411/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-06-13","Army Foundation College","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to the Answer of 12 June 2018 to Question 150193 on Army Foundation College, if he will provide that data for the last three years.","false","Biography information for Liz Saville Roberts","Dwyfor Meirionnydd","Liz Saville Roberts","153416"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923413","Treasury","false","2018-06-18","<p>The information requested is not readily available and could be provided only at disproportionate cost.</p>","Newark","Robert Jenrick","153304 ; 153368","2018-06-18T15:31:09.773Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923413/answer","Biography information for Robert Jenrick","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923413/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923413/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2018-06-13","Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how much his Department has spent on preparations for inter-governmental discussions in relation to negotiations with the EU in 2018 to date.","false","Biography information for Drew Hendry","Inverness, Nairn, Badenoch and Strathspey","Drew Hendry","153374"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923414","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-06-20","<p>Nuclear power is proven technology with modern reactors capable of producing safe and secure low carbon electricity over many decades. Reactors deployed in the UK must meet the robust independent regulatory requirements which include early assessment of the safety, security and environmental impacts of reactor designs through the Generic Design Assessment (GDA), prior to any application for a site-specific statutory Nuclear Site Licence. This is a robust process, taking several years which ensures that all aspects of new station design are thoroughly assessed prior to construction and operation.</p><p> </p><p>Hitachi’s UK ABWR reactor design completed GDA in December 2017 and full details of that assessment are available at <a href="http://www.onr.org.uk/new-reactors/uk-abwr/index.htm" target="_blank">www.onr.org.uk/new-reactors/uk-abwr/index.htm</a> .</p>","Watford","Richard Harrington",,"2018-06-20T16:31:13.377Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923414/answer","Biography information for Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923414/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923414/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-06-13","Wylfa Power Station","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what assessment his Department made of Hitachi’s nuclear power safety record in advance of considering private sector involvement in the Wylfa nuclear project.","false","Biography information for Stuart C. McDonald","Cumbernauld, Kilsyth and Kirkintilloch East","Stuart C. McDonald","153322"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923415","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-06-20","<p>The Government regularly engages with a number of new build developers on a range of issues relevant to delivering new nuclear projects including financing. These discussions are commercially sensitive and it is therefore not appropriate to provide details.</p>","Watford","Richard Harrington",,"2018-06-20T16:31:39.097Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923415/answer","Biography information for Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923415/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923415/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-06-13","Sizewell C Power Station","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what discussions his Department had with representatives of EDF Energy on funding options for Sizewell C nuclear power station in Suffolk.","false","Biography information for Stuart C. McDonald","Cumbernauld, Kilsyth and Kirkintilloch East","Stuart C. McDonald","153323"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923416","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-06-20","<p>As part of the process to designate a National Policy Statement (NPS) for nuclear power generation in 2011, the Government undertook a strategic siting assessment of potentially suitable sites, including an Appraisal of Sustainability. The conclusions of these assessments were included in an annex to the final NPS. <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/47860/1943-nps-nuclear-power-annex-volII.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/47860/1943-nps-nuclear-power-annex-volII.pdf</a>.</p><p>The Government is working towards a new NPS for nuclear power stations deploying after 2025 and intends to consult on a draft NPS in 2019. Siting assessments and Appraisals of Sustainability will be undertaken for those sites listed in the draft NPS.</p><p> </p><p>CGN’s UK HPR1000 reactor, which is proposed for deployment at Bradwell, commenced the GDA process in January 2017. More information can be found at <a href="http://www.ukhpr1000.co.uk/" target="_blank">www.ukhpr1000.co.uk/</a>. The GDA is a robust process conducted jointly by the Office of Nuclear Regulation and the Environment Agency over many years, ensuring that all aspects of new station design, including safety, security and environmental impacts, are properly assessed prior to construction and operation.</p>","Watford","Richard Harrington",,"2018-06-20T16:32:02.947Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923416/answer","Biography information for Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923416/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923416/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-06-13","Bradwell B Power Station: Environment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what assessment his Department has made of the environmental effect of Bradwell B nuclear plant in Essex.","false","Biography information for Stuart C. McDonald","Cumbernauld, Kilsyth and Kirkintilloch East","Stuart C. McDonald","153324"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923417","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-06-20","<p>The Government regularly engages with a number of new build developers on a range of issues relevant to delivering new nuclear projects including financing. These discussions are commercially sensitive and it is therefore not appropriate to provide details.</p>","Watford","Richard Harrington",,"2018-06-20T16:32:21.977Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923417/answer","Biography information for Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923417/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923417/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-06-13","Nuclear Power Stations: Construction","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what discussions his Department has had it's counterpart in South Korea on (a) new nuclear power stations in the UK and (b) funding options for Moorside project in Cumbria.","false","Biography information for Stuart C. McDonald","Cumbernauld, Kilsyth and Kirkintilloch East","Stuart C. McDonald","153325"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923418","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-06-21","<p>The availability and reliability of financial backers for the Moorside nuclear project is a commercial matter for Toshiba, who own NuGen, the developer of the Moorside site.</p><p> </p><p>We continue to engage closely with NuGen, as we do for other new build developers on a range of issues relevant to delivering new nuclear projects.</p>","Watford","Richard Harrington",,"2018-06-21T12:43:39.383Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923418/answer","Biography information for Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923418/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923418/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-06-13","Sellafield","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what assessment his Department has made of the (a) availability and (b) reliability of financial backers for Moorside nuclear reactor in Cumbria.","false","Biography information for Stuart C. McDonald","Cumbernauld, Kilsyth and Kirkintilloch East","Stuart C. McDonald","153326"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923420","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-06-20","<p>The Department has engaged with a number of parties with respect to the proposed sale of NuGen, developers of the proposed Moorside project in Cumbria. These discussions are commercially sensitive so we are unable to provide details.</p>","Watford","Richard Harrington",,"2018-06-20T16:32:43.76Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923420/answer","Biography information for Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923420/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923420/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-06-13","Sellafield","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what discussions his Department has had with (a) it's Chinese counterpart and (b) representatives of State Nuclear Power Technology Corporation on the Moorside nuclear reactor project in Cumbria.","false","Biography information for Stuart C. McDonald","Cumbernauld, Kilsyth and Kirkintilloch East","Stuart C. McDonald","153327"
