"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923423","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-06-18","<p>DWP does not have a national commercial relationship with Unum Provident, however at a local level through the Low Value Procurement process there may be local contracts. To identify these would require a search of local provision and could only be achieved at disproportionate cost.</p>","North West Hampshire","Kit Malthouse",,"2018-06-18T14:39:41.727Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923423/answer","Biography information for Kit Malthouse","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923423/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923423/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-06-13","UNUM","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, whether his Department has any commercial relationship with Unum Provident.","false","Biography information for Kevin Brennan","Cardiff West","Kevin Brennan","153210"
