"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923425","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-06-18","<p>While the precise details of our participation in this exercise are yet to be confirmed, on current planning assumptions, the following UK Armed Forces units and personnel are due to participate in Exercise Trident Juncture 2018: from the Naval Service, at least three destroyers and/or frigates, four mine counter measures vessels, a mine warfare battle staff and command platform, and in excess of one Royal Marines Company; from the Army, a Light Mechanised Infantry Task Force led by Headquarters 4th Infantry Brigade with forces principally drawn from 1st Battalion The Royal Irish Regiment, The Light Dragoons, 32 Engineer Regiment, 3rd Regiment Royal Horse Artillery, 2 Signal Regiment, 2 Close Support Battalion Royal Electrical Mechanical Engineers, 6 Regiment The Royal Logistics Corps; from the Royal Air Force, four Hawk aircraft from 100 Squadron based at RAF Leeming.</p><p>It is also expected that in the region of 3,000 Service personnel will deploy on the exercise, subject to our operational requirements.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2018-06-18T16:31:34.48Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923425/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923425/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/923425/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-06-13","NATO: Military Exercises","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, which of the Armed Forces (a) units and (b) ships he plans to participate in Exercise Trident Juncture 18.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","153213"
